FBIS4-6461 "dreas077_c_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 North Korea Groups in Japan Urge Anti-U.S., Antiwar Fight Groups in Japan Urge Anti-U.S., Antiwar Fight SK2004153994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1521 GMT 20 Apr 94 SK2004153994 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 17 (KNS-KCNA) -- The Federation of South Koreans in Japan for Democracy and Reunification, the League of South Korean Youth in Japan and the Democratic Association of South Korean Women in Japan recently issued a joint appeal calling on the 70 million Koreans at home and abroad to unite firmly and rise up courageously in the anti-U.S., anti-war and anti-nuke struggle in order to defend the country and the nation from a scourge of war and achieve peace on the Korean peninsula and national reunification. "The Koreans at home and abroad should lift up critical voices and hold higher the banner of struggle in order to oppose the resumption of the Team Spirit joint military maneuvers, check the shipment of Patriot missiles and frustrate all the military provocations," said the appeal. "All the Koreans who love the country and the nation should join hands and kindle the flames of the anti-U.S., anti-war and anti-nuke struggle."
